libinput (library to handles input devices)

libinput is a library that handles input devices for  display servers
and other applications that need to directly deal with input devices.
It provides  device  detection,  device handling,  input device event
processing  and abstraction.  Input event processing includes scaling
touch coordinates, generating pointer events from touchpads,  pointer
acceleration, etc.

http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/libinput/